#"One of my recent projects is an AI-powered BI dashboard I called BizAI. The problem I wanted to solve is that most business intelligence tools like Tableau or Power BI are expensive, complex, and require training — so non-technical people like business analysts and managers can't access their own data easily.
My solution was a natural language interface. You type a question in plain English — something like 'show me profit margins by category' or 'who are the top sales reps' — and the dashboard instantly updates with the right chart, the right data table, and a written AI insight explaining what the numbers mean.
Technically, I built a custom NLP intent detection engine. It tokenises the input, scores each word against keyword sets for 8 different intents — region, monthly trends, products, anomalies, customer segments and so on — and picks the best match. It then dynamically renders the right chart type — whether that's a line chart, bar chart, doughnut, dual-axis or combo chart.
I also built in anomaly detection using mean and standard deviation — so if you ask it to 'show anomalies', it flags any months where orders are statistically unusual.
The whole thing runs in a single HTML file with no API key, no backend, no install. It's live on my GitHub right now."
