#BizAI is an AI-powered Business Intelligence dashboard that allows anyone to query business data using plain English — no technical skills, no expensive software, and no API key required.
The Problem
Traditional BI tools like Tableau and Power BI are powerful but complex. Business analysts and managers cannot access their own data without technical training or depending on overloaded data teams. BizAI removes that barrier completely.
How It Works
When a user types a query such as "show me sales by region", the dashboard runs it through a custom-built NLP intent detection engine inspired by the VADER sentiment model. First, the query is tokenised and lowercased. Each word is then scored against eight intent rule sets — words like "region" trigger the regional analysis, "monthly" triggers the time series view, 
and "anomaly" triggers statistical outlier detection. The intent with the highest keyword score wins and instantly renders the correct visualisation.
The dashboard supports six chart types — line charts for trends, bar charts for comparisons, doughnut charts for proportions, dual-axis charts for combined metrics, combo charts, and ranked tables. Every query also generates a plain English insight panel explaining what the data means, which region is underperforming, 
which product has the best margin, or which sales rep leads the team.
The Data
The dashboard contains a realistic UK B2B SaaS dataset covering £4.82M annual revenue, 18,340 orders, eight UK regions, six product categories, and a sales representative leaderboard. Anomaly detection uses mean and standard deviation calculations to automatically flag unusual spikes and drops in red.
Technical Stack
Built entirely in vanilla HTML, CSS and JavaScript using Chart.js for visualisations. There is no backend, no framework, no API calls and no installation required. The entire application is a single HTML file that runs directly in any browser — making it instantly shareable, deployable, and accessible to anyone.
